climbs.name: Trespassers Will
climbs.fa: William Maki, Fred Maki, Bryan Baez

content.description: Traverse right and up off the end of Hundred Acre ledge to right facing crack (Bounce 11C will branch off to the right, so stay to the left) and then on to bulging face with good features. Finish off on a short slab to the anchor. Very good exposure, once off of the ledge.
content.protection: Approximately seven bolts and two bolt anchor. Two bolt belay station at start.
content.location: Rappel down to Hunred Acre Ledge to start. Route starts on eastward most side of ledge. If setting up top rope use anchors (one cold shut and one hanger) 10 feet east of Eeyore's anchor.

climbs.name: Pleffalumps
climbs.fa: William Maki, Fred Maki, Bryan Baez

content.description: Climb face with tiny edges to small ledge followed by a second, short face to highly textured slab. Route is covered in lichen making it difficult to maintain solid footing.
content.protection: Bolted route. Approximately 7 bolts and two bolt anchor. There are several good bolts on Hundred Acre Ledge to secure the belayer.
content.location: This route and Eeyore share the same two bolt anchor ( one hanger and one cold shut). Rappel down to Hundred Acre Ledge to start. Right of Eeyore.

climbs.name: Eeyore
climbs.fa: William Maki, Fred Maki, Bryan Baez

content.description: Starts on ledge high above the ground. Short slab with large bulging features to small face. Mantle up on to the second ledge. Continue to follow bolts to anchor.
content.protection: Bolted route, approx 7 bolts. Shares anchor with Pleffalumps.
content.location: Rappel down to Hundred Acre ledge to start. Local guide book indicates this route having its own anchors. If so then they are elusive. Use anchors for Pleffalumps to access ledge. First bolted route on left.
